etymologies: late 16th century; earliest use found in Richard Harvey (d. 1630), astrologer and polemicist. From classical Latin deleatur ‘let it be deleted’, 3rd singular present subjunctive passive of dēlēre

definitions: An instruction or symbol (usually written as ?) used on a page of text to indicate a part which should be deleted; an instance of the use of this instruction. Also (and in earliest use) figurative.
